# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __call__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__call__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __call__.
# asyncio types are not callable as function-like objects. Their API is
#   expressed through coroutine methods (acquire(), release(), get(), put(),
#   wait(), set(), clear()), not __call__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: constructed by the event loop; no __call__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: synchronization guards; no __call__ defined.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards; no __call__ defined.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; no __call__ defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

